com.jivesoftware.selenium.pagefactory.framework.config

Class TimeoutsConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jivesoftware.selenium.pagefactory.framework.config.TimeoutsConfig

  • public final class TimeoutsConfig
extends Object

    Represents the timeout configuration used by a Browser.

    Use TimeoutsConfig.defaultTimeoutsConfig() to get an instance with default timeout values.

    Use TimeoutsConfig.builder() to get a Builder that begins with default timeout values. Then call builder.build() to get a finalized TimeoutsConfig instance.

    See Also:
    TimeoutType

      • builder

        public static TimeoutsConfig.Builder builder()
        Return a Builder for constructing a TimeoutsConfig instance. The Builder is populated with default timeouts, and you can modify them as desired, then call builder.build().
        Returns:
        - a TimeoutsConfig.Builder

      • getTimeoutInSeconds

        public int getTimeoutInSeconds(TimeoutType timeout)
        Return the timeout in seconds for the given TimeoutType. It doesn't make sense to pass in the DEFAULT timeout type, because that is a context-sensitive timeout.
        Parameters:
        timeout - - the TimeoutType (other than DEFAULT) to get the timeout in seconds for.
        Returns:
        - the timeout in seconds
